main event: An observation of a round, bright green object the size of a basketball was reported on 13 Feb 59 near Oak Harbor, Washington.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 2-5 seconds., The object was described as a fireball., Multiple reliable military personnel witnessed the sighting., The object emerged from the water and was sighted at a low altitude., There were concerns about a possible collision with the tower at the Oak Harbor Naval Station.
sighted object: round, bright green object the size of a basketball
